        "what": "Suzhou-style mung bean soup — a clear mint broth with glutinous rice, candied dates, winter melon candy, and colorful threads — shocked northern Chinese who only know the mushy boiled version. The debate drove 898M heat and 320% order surge in Suzhou.",
        "data": "5.8B total views, 3.2B in 48h. Comment rate 18.7% vs food category average 8.2%. Geographic spread: Jiangsu 28% → Guangdong 15%. 27 new shops opened in one week. Delivery orders surged 320% WoW.",
        "analysis": "Three virality triggers: (1) Cognitive dissonance as #1 food content driver — Zibo BBQ and Tianshui spicy hot pot followed same pattern. (2) Local IP × seasonal demand dual-engine. (3) Low decision-cost (¥15-30) enables instant purchase. Reference Zibo BBQ timeline: March emergence → April surge → May peak → June stabilization.",
        "takeaway": "Creators: comparative challenges deliver highest engagement. Post daily for 7 days to capture full trend wave. Brands: beverage companies should evaluate within 2-4 week window. Sellers: soup ingredient kits are lowest-barrier monetization — ¥5-8 cost, ¥29.9 retail for 3-pack."
